# AGENTS.md

> One file to rule them all. Harnesses (Claude Code, arc-agents, Hermes, etc.) read this file
> to understand the repo's goals, agent bindings, and operating constraints.
> In Claude Code: symlink CLAUDE.md → AGENTS.md (Windows: `mklink /J CLAUDE.md AGENTS.md`).

## Mission

<!-- One paragraph. What done looks like. What the constraints are. -->

## Director bindings

<!-- Director reads these on boot. Prompts for any missing entry and writes the answer back. -->

event-bus: jsonl              # jsonl (.arc/events.jsonl) | db | <skill-name>
task-delegation: native       # native (harness agent tool) | arc-agents | <skill-name>
workspace: worktree           # worktree | treehouse | <skill-name>
on-task-verified: draft-pr    # merge | draft-pr | <skill-name>
todo-list: native             # native | arc-agents | <skill-name>
feedback-sink: jsonl          # jsonl (.arc/feedback.jsonl) | <api-url> | <skill-name>

budget:
  weekly: 500k                # tokens/week; resets Monday 00:00 UTC
  bypass:
    - critical-failure        # qa.failed with dimension: critical-failure
    - security                # qa.failed with dimension: security

## Worker agents

